    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Study and practice of the use of selected books and other readings for therapeutic purposes to promote an individual's mental or physical health or development; often used as an adjunct to psychotherapy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estudio y práctica de usar libros seleccionados y otras lecturas para propósitos terapéuticos para promover la salud o desarrollo físico o mental de un individuo, a menudo usado en conjunto con la psicoterapia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De studie en de praktijk van het gebruik van geselecteerde boeken en ander leesmateriaal voor therapeutische doeleinden om de geestelijke of lichamelijke gezondheid of ontwikkeling van een individu te bevorderen. Vaak gebruikt in combinatie met psychotherapie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052536/Psychologisch woordenboek En-Ne (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以所選定之書籍或其他閱讀材料作為治療用途，目的為提升個人身心健康或發展的研究與實務；通常為心理治療中的附屬程序。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
